U . S . spot gas prices continue to erode on weather . U . S . spot natural gas prices continued to weaken Friday ahead of the holiday weekend and milder temperatures next week , industry sources said . Louisiana Gulf Coast prices fell another 10 cents to the $ 2 . 10 - 2 . 15 per million British thermal units range , while prices in south Texas dropped 20 cents to the mid - $ 1 . 90s to low - $ 2 area . Temperatures are expected to be above - normal throughout most of the U . S . by Tuesday of next week following a brief cold spell in the East on Sunday and Monday . 
